results.description: Kanda is an area in northeastern Chiyoda, Tokyo, Japan. It encompasses about thirty neighborhoods. This photo was taken in one of them called "Uchi-Kanda," which is near Kanda Station. The Kanda area has a large concentration of small, older buildings and lots of alleyways like this one. As you can see, the streets are kept very clean and neat considering the population density. It is considered safe to walk around at all hours.
